 sources in the VLBI sub-sample based on the distances derived from maser\nparallaxes, and derived a new bolometric period-luminosity relation for\nGalactic oxygen-rich Mira variables. A new distance catalogue based on these\nresults is provided for the sources in the DEATHSTAR sample. We found that a\nRUWE (re-normalised unit weight error) below 1.4 does not guarantee reliable\ndistance estimates and we advise against the use of only the RUWE to measure\nthe quality of Gaia DR3 astrometric data for individual AGB stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Sep 2022 16:23:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 23 Sep 2022 09:26:20 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 7 Nov 2022 11:10:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-09"}
